<figureCitation id="78F42A63A70AD66678DA69B4DD5C4481" box="[490,620,1689,1715]" captionStart="Fig 6" captionStartId="12.[189,230,1807,1833]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-11@12.[189,1398,269,1754]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig 6. Carrhotus atratus sp. nov. A–B. Male habitus. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus.C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. E–F. Palp. E. Ventral view. F. Retrolateral view. G. Epigynum. Abbreviations: E = embolus; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis. Scale bars: A–D = 2 mm; E–F = 0.2 mm; G = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518321/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="84">Figs 6E–F</figureCitation>
, 
